newsitem.title: AUSTRIA: Austrian bonds end higher on positive U.S. data.
newsitem.headline: Austrian bonds end higher on positive U.S. data.

text.p: 1600 GMT - Austrian bonds firmed on Tuesday, tracking German bunds after a healthy set of U.S. data indicating subdued inflation, and traders said the trend was likely to remain positive in the near future.
Traders said Austria's new 10-year 5.625 bond, issued earlier on Tuesday, had been taken up well by the market.
* 10 year benchmark 5.875 pct bond maturing July 2006 down 10 bps at 100.20 to yield 5.84 (5.83) pct in bourse trade, quoted post-market at 100.47/57 to yield 5.80/79.
* At the near end, five-year 5.50 percent bond maturing March 2001 up 10 bps at 103.75 to yield 4.54 (4.57) percent in bourse trade, quoted post-market at 103.91/104.01 to yield 4.50/48 percent.
* AGB future up 37 bps at 107.95 on turnover of 455 lots.
* 10-year spread to German bunds up two at five bp, five-year spread up one at 14 bps.
* Money market rates mixed with three-month VIBOR steady at 3.350 and overnight money lower at 3.13/3.38.
